    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p> To my great comfort <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Lows</persName> draft is just arrived, which I shall pay on Saturday. I
                    leave town on Monday. I do assure you the fault about the delivery of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Books rests on <persName ref="pe0309">your master
                        of the ship</persName>.</p>
                <p>Be so good as to return the Letter I sent undirected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am in much <lb/>haste y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>

                <dateline>April 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1774.</dateline>

                <postscript>
                    <p> I think you had best order some ship master to call at <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Whites</persName> for the
                        box of <bibl type="authorial">
                            <title ref="bi0004 bi0008">my Tours</title>
                        </bibl>
                        that you are so kind as to disperse. </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
